#Histogram: hist(x)
#Boxplot: boxplot(x)
#Density plot: plot(density(x))
x.norm <- rnorm(100, mean=0, sd=1) 
hist(x.norm)

boxplot(x.norm)

plot(density(x.norm))

#Barchart: barplot(x)
#Piechart: pie(x) 
x <- sample(c(1:8), 100, replace=TRUE, prob=c(8:1)) 
x <- table(x) 
names(x) <- c("A", "B", "C", "D", "E", "F", "G", "H") 
barplot(x)

pie(x)

x <- rnorm(100) 
y <- 3*x + rnorm(100, 0, 1) 
plot(x, y)

cor(x,y)

#Add text
x <- rnorm(50) 
y <- 3*x + rnorm(50, 0, 1) 
y1 <- 5*x + rnorm(50, 0, 2)
plot(x, y, type = "p", pch = 19) 
abline(a = 0, b = 3)
points(x, y1, col = 4, pch = 20) 
abline(a = 0, b = 5, col = 4)
text(-1.5, 2, "A", cex = 5) 
text(1, -5, "B", cex = 5, col = 2) 
legend("topleft", c("Y", "Y1"), col = c(1,4), lty = c(1, 1), cex = 2)
#re-arrange the region of a figure
x <- rnorm(50) 
y <- 3*x + rnorm(50, 0, 1) 
y1 <- 5*x + rnorm(50, 0, 2)

plot(x, y, type = "p", pch = 19) 
abline(a = 0, b = 3)
points(x, y1, col = 4, pch = 20) 
abline(a = 0, b = 5, col = 4)

text(1, -5, "B", cex = 5, col = 2)

#layout(matrix(c(1,2,3,3),2,2,byrow=TRUE)
x <- rnorm(50) 
y <- 3*x + rnorm(50, 0, 1) 
y1 <- 5*x + rnorm(50, 0, 2)
y2 <- -2*x + rnorm(50, 0, 2)
layout(matrix(c(1,2,3,3), 2, 2, byrow=TRUE)) 
plot(x, y, type = "p", pch = 19, main = "Y") 
abline(a = 0, b = 3) 
plot(x, y1, type = "p", pch = 19, main = "Y1") 
abline(a = 0, b = 5)
